    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469\">\n<html><head>\n \n</head> \n\n \n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Thank you for making me more \nefficient :)&nbsp; There are so many ways&nbsp;we can do same things in JUnit \nthat&nbsp;I tend to stop discovering as soon as I have something working . \n</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">This is certainly a more \nelegant way of writing tests for Exception handling.</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Cheers,</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Sachin</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote><span title=\"qreply\"> <blockquote>\n  <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469OutlookMessageHeader\" dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"\n size=\"2\">-----Original Message-----<br><b>From:</b> Brian Button \n  [mailto:bbutton01@...]<br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, December 19, 2000 \n  9:08 PM<br><b>To:</b> junit@egroups.com<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [junit] \n  Exception Handling Question<br><br></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">I agree with what Sachin \n  said, with one minor change. There is another member function in Assert called \n  fail() which you can use:</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\"></span></font>&nbsp;</div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">public void testXXX( ) throws \n  Exception</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">{</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; \ntry</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; {</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n  doMyStuffThatMightThrow( );</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fail( \n  &quot;Didn&#39;t get my expected exception&quot; );</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; }</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; catch( \n  MyExpectedException e )</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; {</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; }</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">}</span></font></div>\n  <div>&nbsp;</div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">Same thing as the previous \n  poster, just replace his assert( false ) with fail().</span></font></div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\"></span></font>&nbsp;</div>\n  <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469269200513-19122000\">bab</span></font></div>\n  <p><font size=\"2\">----<br>Brian Button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n  bbutton@...<br>Senior Consultant&nbsp; Object Mentor, Inc.</font> \n  </p>\n  <blockquote\n style=\"PADDING-LEFT:5px;MARGIN-LEFT:5px;BORDER-LEFT:#000000 2px solid;\">\n    <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469OutlookMessageHeader\" dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"\n size=\"2\">-----Original Message-----<br><b>From:</b> sachin gupta \n    [mailto:sachin@...]<br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, December 19, 2000 \n    12:29 AM<br><b>To:</b> junit@egroups.com<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [junit] \n    Exception Handling Question<br><br></font></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">In case Exception is \n    mentioned in the throws clause of method you may try something like this \n    </font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">try </font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">{</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font size=\"2\">method \n    with input that causes the expected Exception to be \n    thrown.</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n    assert(false);</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">}</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">catch (ExpectedException \n    e)</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">{</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font\n size=\"2\">assert(true);</font></span></div>\n    <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-255052469992582106-19122000\"><font\n size=\"2\">}</font></span></div></blockquote><br><br><tt>To \n  unsubscribe from this group, send an email \n  to:<br>junit-unsubscribe@egroups.com<br><br></tt><br></blockquote></span></blockquote></html> \n</div>", 
